de.oaam.model.oaam.functions

Interface Input

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, ModeDependentElementA, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, OaamBaseElementA, VariantDependentElementA
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    InputImpl

    public interface Input
extends OaamBaseElementA, VariantDependentElementA, ModeDependentElementA
    A representation of the model object 'Input'. An input of a function is the need for data to be operational

    The following features are supported:

    • Declaration
    • Implements
    • Io Bindings
    • Queue Length
    • Output Link
    See Also:
    FunctionsPackage.getInput()

      • getQueueLength

        int getQueueLength()
        Returns the value of the 'Queue Length' attribute. The default value is "0". The number of inputs remembered while the task processes the first arriving input. 0 = drops all inputs till the task is ready. 1 = stores exactly one input. n > 1 = stores n inputs which are executed afterwards.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Queue Length' attribute.
        See Also:
        setQueueLength(int), FunctionsPackage.getInput_QueueLength()
